```js
if (!("repository" in context.payload)) {
  return
}
const owner = context.payload.repository?.owner?.login;
if (!owner) {
  return
}
```
but I think `getDeepValue` reduces type safety because you have to specify the return type and can introduce bugs because you can make a typo and there won't be any warnings

