@whilefoo wouldn't there be only one that would technically close the pull-request? Even if two (or more) people are assigned, could they have two separate pull-requests?
Actually there is logic to reopen an issue and not generate if multiple requests are opened and marked as "Resolves" against the issue: https://github.com/ubiquity-os-marketplace/text-conversation-rewards/blob/a602dbacbce2425cf43d81015c29073a35915ff3/src/run.ts#L38
I added this a while ago to handle the case where many pull-requests are needed from different repositories to really finish a task, never tried with multiple assignees however.

